pos_mean_info_list.mean: 获得；了解（get的现在分词）；抓住

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指通过中间人传递信息，或以某种方式把人或物送到目的地。
指一往一返，相当于go and bring，去取了东西或带人再返回到出发处。
口语用词，与fetch基本同义，语气随便。
指使用车辆或机械设备把人或货物从一处运载到另一处。
指从说话人或说话人心目中所在处把某人或某物带离开，带到离说话者有一定距离的地方，与bring的方向正相反，侧重方向，不着重方式。
指从某处把人或物带到或拿到说话者所在的地点，强调方向，不着重方式。
指把物品从一个地方带到另一个地方，不涉及方向，只强调方式。
强调通过不断的、持续的努力而获得某物，也指日积月累地渐渐地获得。书面语用词。
较正式用词，着重通过巨大努力、要求而得到所需或盼望已久的东西。
普通用词，使用广泛，可指以任何方式得到某物，也不一定要经过努力。
强调要通过努力或竞争，或需要付出代价才能获得所渴望的东西。
主要指通过努力、斗争、比赛等而获得胜利。
侧重指依靠自己的劳动或因付出代价与有功而获得。
侧重指经过努力或有意识行动而取得某种成就或获得某种利益或好处。
正式用词，侧重指使某事发生的原因。
侧重指劝某人做某事，或指使某事物处于某种状态或产生某种结果。
普通用词，指让某人做某事。
普通用词，指强迫或劝诱他人做某事。
书面用词，多指因外界因素而使某人或某物处于某种状态。
侧重指变得与原来截然不同，有时含贬义。
常指某人或某物有意无意地获得引起变化的因素，结果使变成另一状态。
常指逐渐地变成新状态，强调渐变的过程。
最普通用词，作为连系动词，指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
侧重变化的经过或过程，多用于不良情况。
作为连系动词，通常与形容词连用，指进入某种状态，从而发生变化，多指不好的状态。
为正式用词，多用于庄重场合，主要指通过努力达到重要目的或得到珍贵的东西。如：The scientist attained great fame by a new discovery.(那科学家由于一次新发现而出了名。)
指通过本身的努力逐渐获得知识、能力和荣誉等。如：acquire knowledge(获得知识)。
多指凭努力或恳求得到急需或很想得到的东西。如：Howard had failed to obtain a scholarship.(霍华德没能得到奖学金。)
用得最广，可指以各种方式获得各种东西。如：Where can I get enough information?(我从哪儿能得到足够的资料？)
多指克服困难后取得胜利，成功，强调“得到”这一结果。如：He achieved his ambition in the end.(他最终实现了他的抱负。)
多指付出极大努力后获得或赢得给自己带来优势的东西。如：They gained the victory after a bloody battle.(浴血奋战后他们赢得了胜利。)

bilingual.source: You get this for a low price.

bilingual.target: 我们从植物中得到什么？

bilingual.source: What do you get from your birthday?
What do you get from your birthdays?
bilingual.target: 你从生日中得到了什么？
你从哪里得到这块桌布的？

bilingual.source: What should I do to get the work?
bilingual.target: 我应该怎么做才能得到这份工作？

list.abstract: get，英语单词，意思有收到、获得，多用于表示感情、气候、环境的变化后接形容词原级或比较级；亦为研究生英语学位考试简称。
Get的核心业务是通过人工对接的方式帮助用户解决生活中能够想得出的烦恼和需求。2015年9月18日，在线私人助理“Get”宣布获得660万美元A轮融资，融资由鼎辉资本和执一资本联合投资。

yingyinNormal.en: How ya gonna get it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你打算怎么得到呢？

yingyinNormal.en: What? Wait. Why, why do you get the story?
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？等一下，你为什么要得到这个故事？

yingyinNormal.en: How could I not get that part? Stupid Ralph Macchio.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我怎么没得到那部分？愚蠢的拉夫.马切奥。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you get if you take a circle and sweep it out in three dimensions? You get a sphere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果在三维空间你画个圈，并把它扫描出来，你会得到什么？你会得到一个球体。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Charlie's gonna get that. Hey, don't say that. You've got just as good a chance of getting that job.
yingyinNormal.zh: 查理会得到的。嘿，别那样说。你也有机会得到那工作的。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. I have four hours to get the impossible manuscript. Smith&Wollensky's doesn't open until 11:30. How am I gonna get the steak?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，四个小时内得到不可能得到的手稿，SW 牛排店十一点半才开门，要去哪儿买牛排？

yingyinNormal.en: This is all you get. You get me, and you get your family, and you get this world, and that's it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你就能得到这么多。你有我，你的家庭，你来过这个世界，仅此而已。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you mean you didn't get the job? How could you not get it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你没得到工作是什么意思？你怎么可能得不到?

yingyinNormal.en: Oh! Pippa Middleton, wow. She was up for a job on "The Today Show," but she didn't get it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 社交名媛啊，她本来有机会在《今日秀》得到工作呢，可惜她最后没得到。

yingyinNormal.en: If I get this. When you get this, you gotta give it everything you got. Everything. It's your dream. What are you gonna do?
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我得到的话。当你得到时，你必须抛开一切，竭尽全力地努力。竭尽全力，这是你的梦想。那你要做什么呢？

yingyinNormal.en: You want a pat on the back, you better get a longer arm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想得到别人的鼓励是不可能的。

yingyinNormal.en: You get Ramsey, you get the God's Eye. You get Shaw. Well that's the windup and the pitch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只要找到拉姆齐，你就能得到天眼，也就能找到肖了，一切就是这么水到渠成。

yingyinNormal.en: Then you should get it. I will get it. If you could just help me out a little bit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你应该得到这个机会。我会的，只要你稍微帮我一点忙…

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Leonard, do you think your mom would be available? Yeah, you don't want to do that. Talking to my mom to get more confidence is like talking to a lion to get more alive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱纳德，你觉得你母亲会有空吗？你不会想找她谈的。想跟我妈聊天来得到信心就跟去找阎王聊天来得到生存感一样。

yingyinNormal.en: I just think in relationships you get back what you put into them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得感情上你付出多少才能得到多少。

yingyinNormal.en: We'll make sure you and your family get the support you need.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们将确保你和你的家人能够得到你需要的。

yingyinNormal.en: It gives us certain happiness that we just don't get other purchases.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们从中得到的快乐是从别的物品得不到的。

yingyinNormal.en: Jesus. Where did you get it? In my mailbox just after she died.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天啊，你从哪里得到的？她死后在我邮箱里找到的。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, you know what, you're gonna get it. I can feel it. Can you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道吗, 你会得到工作的，我能感觉到。你能吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And what does that get them? We can buy and sell their business.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那他们得到了什么呢？我们都可以买断他们的生意了。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: If the criterion changed to safety, you would <highlight>get</highlight> more cautious drivers who obeyed traffic laws.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果把标准改为安全性，你将会看到更加谨慎且遵守交通规则的司机。

examination_example.sentence: There, as people <highlight>got</highlight> more money, some of them may have more cleared land for cattle to raise for meat, Ferraro says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 费拉罗说，在那里，当人们得到更多的钱，他们中的一些人可能会有更多的空地为了吃肉来饲养牲畜。

examination_example.sentence: Millions of Britons will nonetheless have <highlight>got</highlight> a share this weekend of one of that nation's great traditions: the Sunday roast.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 本周末数百万英国人仍然会举家共享该国的一大传统：星期日烤肉。

sense_info_list.en: enter or reach a specified state or condition; become

examination_example.sentence: Sometimes parents <highlight>get</highlight> exhausted and frustrated and are unable to maintain a tolerant and composed style with their kids.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时候，父母会变得疲惫和沮丧，无法对孩子保持宽容和沉稳的风格。

examination_example.sentence: Its inherent problems are <highlight>getting</highlight> worse.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它的内在问题正变得越来越严重。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Get</highlight> clear on what impact you're hoping to have.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 弄清楚你希望产生什么样的影响。

sense_info_list.zh: 使...(被处理); 让(某人)去做...

examination_example.sentence: In fact, rushing to <highlight>get</highlight> your own ideas out there can cause colleagues to feel you don't value their opinions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，急于表达自己的想法会让同事觉得你不重视他们的意见。

examination_example.sentence: Here are some ways that you can <highlight>get</highlight> the whole office on your side.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是一些可以让办公室所有人都站在你这边的方法。

examination_example.sentence: The TSA is now rushing to <highlight>get</highlight> new screeners on the line.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今TSA正在急于获取新的安检器材。

sense_info_list.zh: 与过去分词连用构成被动语态

examination_example.sentence: Kids tend to <highlight>get</highlight> stuck in the features and the immediate benefits to them personally, Norris said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Norris说，孩子们往往会被这些特征和对他们个人的眼前利益所迷惑。

examination_example.sentence: Newport also recommends "deep scheduling" to combat constant interruptions and <highlight>get</highlight> more done in less time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Newport还建议“深度计划”以对抗持续的干扰，用更少的时间做更多的事情。

examination_example.sentence: Conversations are links, which means when you have a conversation with a new person a link <highlight>gets</highlight> formed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对话是一种链接形式，这意味着当你和一个刚认识的人进行对话时，链接就形成了。

sense_info_list.zh: 进入; 陷入; 移动

examination_example.sentence: The Times shouldn't waste time <highlight>getting</highlight> out of the print business, but only if they go about doing it the right way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《纽约时报》不应该把时间浪费在退出印刷业上，但前提是他们的做法是正确的。

examination_example.sentence: They have demonstrated that when companies <highlight>get</highlight> into trouble with the law, evidence of good character can win them a less costly punishment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们已经证明，当公司陷入法律困境时，良好品行的证据可以为他们赢得成本较低的惩罚。

examination_example.sentence: Public-sector unions seldom <highlight>get</highlight> in trouble for their actions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公共部门的工会很少因为他们的行为而惹上麻烦。

sense_info_list.zh: 来到; 使到达; 取得进展

examination_example.sentence: It is hard to <highlight>get</highlight> right, and requires a remarkable degree of vision.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个做法很难达到正确，需要非凡的远见。

examination_example.sentence: It has not <highlight>gotten</highlight> anywhere close to that, and one big reason is sticker shock.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但到目前为止，这还远远不够，一个主要原因是高昂的票价。

examination_example.sentence: If they <highlight>get</highlight> by without being filled, we will have wasted them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因为如果没有把它们填满，我们就会浪费掉它们。

examination_example.sentence: Overwhelming majorities of both groups said they believe it is harder for young people today to <highlight>get</highlight> started in life than it was for earlier generations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 两个群体中绝大多数人都表示，他们认为如今的年轻人比以前的几代人更难开始生活。

examination_example.sentence: Young people who are still <highlight>getting</highlight> started in life were more likely than older adults to prioritize personal fulfillment in their work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与年长的成年人相比，仍处于人生起步阶段的年轻人更有可能在工作中优先考虑个人实现。

examination_example.sentence: In February the FTC and Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA) agreed that the industry would <highlight>get</highlight> cracking on responding to DNT requests.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2月，美国联邦贸易委员会和数字广告联盟(DAA)同意，该行业将着手应对DNT请求。

examination_example.sentence: It sends a mixed message, and your counterpart <highlight>gets</highlight> to choose what signals to read.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它发出了一个混杂的信息，你的对手可以选择解读哪一个信号。

examination_example.sentence: For women who stay home, they never <highlight>get</highlight> to leave the office.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于呆在家里的女性来说，她们永远无法离开办公室。

examination_example.sentence: You never really <highlight>get</highlight> to go home from home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你从来没有真正从家里回到家。

sense_info_list.zh: (get back)回来; 返回; 恢复

examination_example.sentence: Although it can be a workout on its own, if your goal is to <highlight>get</highlight> back to tennis or any other activity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你的目标是恢复网球或其他活动，那么它本身就是一种锻炼。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Getting</highlight> back into exercise can be a challenge in the best of times.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在最好的情况下，重新开始锻炼可能是一个挑战。

examination_example.sentence: We still have a long way to go to <highlight>get</highlight> back to full employment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要恢复充分就业，我们还有很长的路要走。

sense_info_list.zh: (get along/on)相处融洽; 和睦相处

examination_example.sentence: Think about how tough it is to <highlight>get</highlight> together 15 people, much less 50, who all <highlight>get</highlight> along perfectly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 想想把15个人聚集在一起是多么困难，更不用说50个人了，而且他们都相处得很好。

examination_example.sentence: 70% of us rate ourselves as above average in leadership, 93% in driving and 85% at <highlight>getting</highlight> on well with others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 70%的人认为自己在领导力方面高于平均水平，93%的人认为自己在驾驶方面高于平均水平，85%的人认为自己在与他人相处方面高于平均水平。

examination_example.sentence: Even among those who <highlight>got</highlight> a cold, the ones who felt greater social support and received more frequent hugs had less severe symptoms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 甚至在已经患有感冒的人群中，感受到较多社会支持，较频繁获得拥抱的人的症状也较轻。

examination_example.sentence: Believe it or not, a warm embrace might even help you avoid <highlight>getting</highlight> sick this winter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 信不信由你，一个温暖的拥抱可以帮助你在这个冬天避免生病。

examination_example.sentence: Watch people <highlight>get</highlight> on and show their tickets.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 看人们上车并出示车票。

sense_info_list.zh: (get away)走开; 离开; 逃脱

examination_example.sentence: Generally however British land artists preferred to <highlight>get</highlight> away from towns.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，一般来说，英国土地艺术家更喜欢远离城镇。

examination_example.sentence: It is easy for children to <highlight>get</highlight> used to blank expressions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子们很容易习惯空白的表情。

examination_example.sentence: Teachers' unions have fought against <highlight>getting</highlight> rid of bad ones and promoting good ones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教师工会一直反对解雇坏教师，提拔好教师。

examination_example.sentence: Maybe you haven't finished thinking the problem through, or you want to <highlight>get</highlight> a clearer sense of what the group thinks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也许你还没有完全思考完这个问题，或者你想更清楚地了解团队的想法。

sense_info_list.zh: 计算后得出(数字或答案)

word_usage.usage: get there除了表示到达某地，还可以表示“达到目的；获得成功”
get out除了表示“外出；逃离”还可以表示“泄露；被人知道”
get through sth.可以表示“消耗掉；用完；耗尽”，还可以表示“（使）正式通过，获得采纳；顺利通过（考试等）”
get用作系动词，get+过去分词可构成系表结构，表示变为某种状态，如get drunk喝醉了、get used to习惯、 get surprised吃惊。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指人的感情、身体状况，或者自然、社会向好的或坏的方面变化，get在日常英语中常用得多。
一般指事物颜色的变化，常指物体或人变得不好。
是正式用语，用于指颜色、天气或人的行为的变化。
指人的感情、身体状况，或者自然、社会向好的或坏的方面变化，一般用于正式文体。

sense_info_list.zh: 得到; 获得; 收到

examination_example.sentence: But I think when we <highlight>get</highlight> feedback from someone we trust, we understand that the feedback isn't some kind of personal attack.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但我认为，当我们从我们信任的人那里得到反馈时，我们会明白，这些反馈并不是某种人身攻击。

examination_example.sentence: It wasn't their skill set or other merits that <highlight>got</highlight> them the job.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 并不是他们的技能或其他优点让他们得到了这份工作。

examination_example.sentence: We have always looked to <highlight>get</highlight> the best things we can as a sort of survival of the fittest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为适者生存的一种方式，我们一直希望得到最好的东西。

sense_info_list.en: move to a different place or into a different position

examination_example.sentence: I couldn't wait to <highlight>get</highlight> out of there once my contract expired.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一旦合同到期，我就迫不及待地想离开哪里。

sense_info_list.zh: 变得; 成为; 开始(感觉到、认识到)

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>get</highlight> much better prepared for school.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们为上学做了更好的准备。

examination_example.sentence: I am reminded of Abraham Lincoln's quote, "I don't like that man. I must <highlight>get</highlight> to know him better."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我想起了亚伯拉罕·林肯的名言，“我不喜欢那个人。我必须进一步了解他。”

examination_example.sentence: The topic <highlight>gets</highlight> more complicated when we talk about the divide between rural and urban communities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们谈到农村和城市社区的区别时，这个话题就变得更加复杂了。

examination_example.sentence: Preschool children really don't <highlight>get</highlight> the moral of the story.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学龄前儿童真的不明白这个故事的寓意。

examination_example.sentence: This will help children interpret and <highlight>get</highlight> the message and help them learn to watch the show for those messages.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将有助于儿童理解和理解这些中心思想，并帮助他们学习观看节目以抓到这些中心思想。

examination_example.sentence: Why can't preschool children <highlight>get</highlight> the moral conveyed in the TV programs?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为什么学龄前儿童不能理解电视节目中传达的道德？

sense_info_list.en: to cause something to happen or be done

examination_example.sentence: In today's talk, we'll discuss how managers can <highlight>get</highlight> their staff to do what they are asked.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在今天的谈话中，我们将讨论经理们如何让他们的员工去做他们被要求做的事情。

examination_example.sentence: Much to their frustration, managers often struggle to <highlight>get</highlight> their staff to comply with even simple instructions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 令人沮丧的是，即使是简单的指示，管理者也常常难以让员工遵守。

examination_example.sentence: Nicole admitted she was fortunate, as she was able to live with her parents and overhaul her spending—and life—to <highlight>get</highlight> herself on track financially.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 妮可承认她很幸运，因为她可以和父母住在一起，彻底改变了她的花费——和生活——让自己在经济上走上正轨。

examination_example.sentence: I <highlight>got</highlight> a throat infection and had to go to the hospital to get some antibiotics as I really wasn't getting any better.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我喉咙感染了，不得不去医院拿些抗生素，因为我真的没有好转。

sense_info_list.zh: (get by)勉强过活; 勉强实现

examination_example.sentence: They do not realize or do not want to realize that many farm families barely managed to <highlight>get</highlight> by on what they grow.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们没有意识到，或者也不想意识到，许多农民家庭仅靠他们种植的作物勉强维持生计。

sense_info_list.zh: (get sth. off one's chest)一吐为快

examination_example.sentence: Perhaps it'll be better <highlight>getting</highlight> things off my chest by going to one of those rate-your-employer websites.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也许去那些给你的雇主打分的网站把我的心事一吐为快会更好。

examination_example.sentence: You certainly <highlight>get</highlight> to travel to some very exotic locations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你当然可以去一些非常吸引人的地方旅行。

word_usage.usage: “get+宾语+动词不定式”表示“让某人做某事”，“to”不能省略。
“get+宾语+过去分词”表示“使某事发生”。
get表“到达”时，属不及物动词，后接宾语时必须先加介词to，但如果后接副词，则不加介词。
get是瞬间动词，其现在完成式不可与表示一段时间的状语连用。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 强调通过不断的、持续的努力而获得某物, 也指日积月累地渐渐地获得。书面语用词。如：acquire knowledge(获得知识)。
为正式用词, 多用于庄重场合, 主要指通过努力达到重要目的或得到珍贵的东西。如：The scientist attained great fame by a new discovery.(那科学家由于一次新发现而出了名。)
侧重指依靠自己的劳动或因付出代价与有功而获得。
侧重指经过努力或有意识行动而取得某种成就或获得某种利益或好处。
普通用词, 使用广泛, 可指以任何方式得到某物, 也不一定要经过努力。
较正式用词, 着重通过巨大努力、要求而得到所需或盼望已久的东西。
普通用词, 含义广泛。强调到达的动作或进程, 不侧重是否到达目的地。也可用于比喻意义。
不及物动词后接 to, get to Beijing。

examination_example.sentence: A research paper rejected by one journal may <highlight>get</highlight> accepted by another.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 被一家期刊拒绝的一篇研究性论文可能会被另一家期刊接受。

examination_example.sentence: And if you <highlight>get</highlight> a broken egg, well, that could happen in a conventional shop, too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你的鸡蛋碎了，那么在传统商店里也可能发生。

examination_example.sentence: They are unable to <highlight>get</highlight> rid of their addiction without professional help.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有专业的援助，他们不能摆脱毒瘾。

examination_example.sentence: In other words, the rich <highlight>get</highlight> richer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 换句话说，富人越来越富。

examination_example.sentence: The businessmen say that on Earth, beans can easily break apart and <highlight>get</highlight> burned in the roaster.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 商人说，在地球上，豆子很容易碾碎并被烘烤机烤焦。

examination_example.sentence: If you <highlight>get</highlight> sick in your stomach within the next 24 hours, you are lacking in the proteins to digest milk.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你在接下来的24小时内感到胃部不适，说明你缺乏消化牛奶的蛋白质。

sense_info_list.en: move to a different place or into a different position

examination_example.sentence: An 81-year-old man ended up in Germany by accident after trying to <highlight>get</highlight> from Newcastle, Great Britain, to Rome, Italy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一名81岁的男子打算从英国纽卡斯尔前往意大利罗马，却意外来到了德国。

examination_example.sentence: It may <highlight>get</highlight> in the way of enhancing one's social status.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它可能会妨碍人提高自己的社会地位。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Get</highlight> outside, stretch your legs, do something cultural, buy yourself something tasty to eat or something pretty to wear.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 出去走走，伸伸腿，做些有文化的事情，给自己买些好吃的或者好看的衣服。

examination_example.sentence: People <highlight>got</highlight> into conversations with us.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们开始和我们交谈。

examination_example.sentence: "Having that sort of curiosity is almost like a protective gear from <highlight>getting</highlight> into boredom," she says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “拥有这种好奇心几乎就像是防止无聊的保护装置，”她说。

examination_example.sentence: He told us he'd <highlight>got</highlight> into an accident.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他告诉我们他出了事故。

examination_example.sentence: You have to <highlight>get</highlight> across what it is about a particular area that has inspired you.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你必须了解激发你灵感的特定领域。

examination_example.sentence: Students who just miss <highlight>getting</highlight> into top high schools or universities do just as well later in life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 错过进入顶级高中或大学的学生在以后的生活中也一样。

examination_example.sentence: If you weren't changing companies every three or four years, you simply weren't <highlight>getting</highlight> ahead in your career.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你不是每三、四年换一家公司，你的职业生涯就根本没有在进步。

examination_example.sentence: As it connects things, your brain turns them into a story, and you <highlight>get</highlight> a dream.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当它把事情联系起来时，你的大脑把它们变成一个故事，你就得到了一个梦。

examination_example.sentence: Here they are learning to <highlight>get</highlight> in touch with their true feelings.

examination_example.sentence: How will the woman <highlight>get</highlight> back from the railway station?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那个女人怎么从火车站回来？

examination_example.sentence: One thing is for certain —Larry went above and beyond the call of duty by <highlight>getting</highlight> so close to the burning vehicle!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一件事是肯定的——拉里如此接近燃烧的汽车，超出了他的职责范围！

examination_example.sentence: In the 1960s we couldn't <highlight>get</highlight> away from home far enough or fast enough to prove we could do it on our own.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在20世纪60年代，无法离家足够远或足够快，以证明我们可以自己独立。

examination_example.sentence: The amazing thing about the spring is that the colder the temperature <highlight>gets</highlight>, the hotter the spring!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 春天的神奇之处在于，温度越低，春天就越热！

examination_example.sentence: Things quickly <highlight>got</highlight> very intense due to the huge amount of energy required to look after them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事情很快变得非常紧张，因为需要大量的精力来照顾它们。

examination_example.sentence: It will undoubtedly help you <highlight>get</highlight> refreshed!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这无疑会让你精神焕发！

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Getting</highlight> to know where essential campus resources are will make your first few weeks on campus a lot easier.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 了解重要的校园资源在哪里，会让你在学校的头几周更容易。

examination_example.sentence: When we were asleep we had to contain them in a large room, otherwise they'd <highlight>get</highlight> up to mischief.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们睡觉时，必须把它们关在一个大房间里，否则它们就会开始胡闹。

examination_example.sentence: To learn to use social media, because it allows them to <highlight>get</highlight> to know the outside world better.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学会使用社交媒体，因为这能让他们更好地了解外面的世界。

word_usage.usage:
(1)后接宾语：The driver will come to get you at 7.司机七点来接你。
(2)后接双宾语：Will you get me a ticket (=get a ticket for me) ?你给我弄张票好吗?
(3)接复合宾语:
①接过去分词作宾补：Why don't you get your shoes mended?你怎么不(请人)把鞋补一下?
②接动词不定式作宾补：We must get them to come over here.我们得让他们到这儿来。
③接现在分词作宾补：Can you get the clock going again?你能使钟重新走起来吗?
(4)接形容词作表语：The weather is getting quite warm.天气变得相当暖和了。
(5)接现在分词作表语：It's eight. Let's get going.八点了，咱们出发吧。

examination_example.sentence: In either situation, you will also need to <highlight>get</highlight> some information about the caller, such as their name or company.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这两种情况下，你也将需要获取一些关于来电者的信息，比如他们的名字或公司。

examination_example.sentence: What do you want to <highlight>get</highlight> from the volunteer job?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你想从志愿者工作中得到什么？

examination_example.sentence: Then we check our mobiles from time to time during the meal, to see whether we <highlight>get</highlight> "liked" or not.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后我们在用餐时不时地查看自己的手机，看看自己有没有获得“点赞”。

examination_example.sentence: This 5-year-old boy has such a good sense of direction that he never <highlight>gets</highlight> lost.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个5岁男孩的方向感很强，他从不迷路。

examination_example.sentence: Thanks to their hard work, the Yangtze River is <highlight>getting</highlight> clearer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由于他们的努力，长江越来越清澈了。

examination_example.sentence: Remember that it takes time to <highlight>get</highlight> used to a new place, school and culture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 别忘了适应一个新的地方、学校和文化需要时间。

examination_example.sentence: Call time is usually bright and early, so I try to <highlight>get</highlight> to bed at a reasonable hour.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通话时间通常很早，所以我尽量在合理的时间上床睡觉。

examination_example.sentence: Several days later, the dog <highlight>got</highlight> into mother's room secretly and made a mess there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几天后，狗偷偷溜进妈妈的房间，把那里弄得一团糟。

examination_example.sentence: Students have to <highlight>get</highlight> to the school at 1:55.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学生必须在1:55到达学校。

examination_example.sentence: The staff members are hoping the festival will <highlight>get</highlight> more foreigners and young people to learn more about traditional Chinese culture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 工作人员希望这个节日能让更多的外国人和年轻人更多地了解中国传统文化。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Getting</highlight> English Language Learners to Put Down the Books.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让英语学习者放下书本。

examination_example.sentence: Many cities run campaigns (运动) to <highlight>get</highlight> people to stop wasting water.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多城市开展运动，让人们停止浪费水。

examination_example.sentence: Where did you <highlight>get</highlight> off the bus?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你在哪里下车的？

examination_example.sentence: You can take the No. 2 bus from here and <highlight>get</highlight> off in front of the cinema.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你可以从这里乘2路公共汽车，在电影院前面下车。

examination_example.sentence: Bella didn't <highlight>get</highlight> off the swing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 贝拉没有离开秋千。

examination_example.sentence: I used to get up at half past six, but now I am <highlight>getting</highlight> used to <highlight>getting</highlight> up at seven.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我过去六点半起床，但现在我已经习惯七点起床了。

sense_info_list.en: to become infected with an illness; to suffer from a pain, etc.

examination_example.sentence: "We feel satisfied. I can tell people that I tried my best, and your kids will no longer <highlight>get</highlight> polio."
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我们感到满意。我可以告诉人们，我已经尽了最大的努力，你们的孩子将不再患脊髓灰质炎。”

examination_example.sentence: Some hospitals use big data to predict if a baby who is born too early will <highlight>get</highlight> sick.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些医院使用大数据预测早产婴儿是否会生病。

examination_example.sentence: There are no buses or trains here, so it can be difficult to <highlight>get</highlight> around without a car.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这里没有公共汽车或火车，因此没有汽车很难四处走动。

sense_info_list.en: to cause something to happen or be done

examination_example.sentence: Please work for our community to tell them the importance of <highlight>getting</highlight> vaccinated and help to reduce the worries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 请为我们的社区工作，告诉他们接种疫苗的重要性，并帮助减少担忧。

examination_example.sentence: After the first injection, you have to <highlight>get</highlight> the second one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第一次注射后，你必须注射第二次。

examination_example.sentence: At stations in some remote (偏远) areas, passengers still need a paper ticket to <highlight>get</highlight> on a train.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在一些偏远地区的车站，乘客仍然需要纸质车票才能上火车。

examination_example.sentence: The movements are similar to traditional Cossack activities, for example, sword fighting and <highlight>getting</highlight> on and off horses.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些运动类似于传统的哥萨克活动，例如，击剑和上下马匹。

sense_info_list.en: used to say that something happens or exists

examination_example.sentence: For example, if you <highlight>get</highlight> something in your eyes, don't start rubbing (揉) it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，如果你眼睛里有东西，不要揉它

sense_info_list.zh: (get in the way)妨碍; 碍事

examination_example.sentence: But they can <highlight>get</highlight> in the way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但他们可能会碍事。

examination_example.sentence: A sanitarium is meant for people who are ill for a long time or who are <highlight>getting</highlight> over a serious illness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 疗养院是为长期生病或正在从重病中恢复过来的人准备的。

examination_example.sentence: They can't <highlight>get</highlight> on well with their classmates, while others may worry about their exams.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们和同学相处不融洽，而其他人可能会担心他们的考试。

examination_example.sentence: How are you <highlight>getting</highlight> on?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你过得怎么样？

word_usage.usage: “get+宾语+动词不定式”表示“让某人做某事”，“to”不能省略。
“get+宾语+过去分词”表示“使某事发生”。
get表“到达”时，属不及物动词，后接宾语时必须先加介词to，但如果后接副词，则不加介词。
get是瞬间动词，其现在完成式不可与表示一段时间的状语连用。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词，使用广泛，可指以任何方式得到某物，也不一定要经过努力。
主要指通过努力、斗争、比赛等而获得胜利。
最普通用词，作为连系动词，指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
常指某人或某物有意无意地获得引起变化的因素，从而变成另一状态。
常指逐渐地变成新状态，强调渐变的过程。
侧重指变得与原来截然不同，有时含贬义。
作为连系动词，通常与形容词连用，指进入某种状态，从而发生变化，多指不好的状态。
侧重变化的经过或过程，多用于不良情况。
指从某处把人或物带到说话者所在的地点，强调方向，不着重方式。
指把物品从一个地方带到另一个地方，不涉及方向，只强调方式。
指从说话人或说话人心目中所在处把某人或某物带离开，带到离说话者有一定距离的地方，与bring的方向正相反，侧重方向，不着重方式。
口语用词，语气随便。
侧重指劝某人做某事，或指使某事物处于某种状态或产生某种结果。
普通用词，指让某人做某事。
